{
  "stem": "3605.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember, one time I saw a-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a father and a child lying in the street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the child was swollen, and the father was asking for a piece of bread or something to eat.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There-- there wasn't much to share.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But anyhow, I gave the father a little bread for the child.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the child did not let me give that back to the father.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He wanted it alone, because he was afraid that maybe the father will eat it up instead of he eat it up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The hunger was so great that some very unusual things happened that you cannot imagine.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About what?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About my own hunger.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I said, as long as I was around my house in my hometown, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we had some belongings that we kept selling and for the money buy some-- some food.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nobody really ate to be full, but just to sustain themselves.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] as I mentioned, our business was taken over by a troy handler, which means a trustee from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had no idea about how to run a business like that, what to do with it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So as a result, he took my father and my brother to work for him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a volksdeutscher who he was from a different town, from Lietsmannstadt, from Lodz, which was in the-- in the Reich.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were in the gubernatorial part of occupation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And every Sunday-- for Sunday, he went to his family, and he sometimes took-- he was a man that besides taking care of his own business, he liked to make some extra money.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So when he went to Lietsmannstadt, we used to give him four coats.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
